I would use a diagram to them and objects that they have seen and used before. I would relate numbers to food such as apples.
I would say there are two apples and after I eat one there is one apple.

Number 7: 00000111
Number 7: 07
Number 7: 7
Number 7 0x7

001    | Number 1: ccs
010    | Number 2: csc
011     | Number 3: css
100    | Number 4: scc
101     | Number 5: scs
110     | Number 6: ssc
111      | Number 7: sss
1000 | Number 8: sccc

Rules:
Take the binary result and replace every 0 with a c and replace every 1 with a s

001       | Number 1: ccs
010       | Number 2: csc
011        | Number 3: css
100       | Number 4: scc
101        | Number 5: scs
110        | Number 6: ssc
111         | Number 7: sss
1000    | Number 8: sccc
1001     | Number 9: sccs
1010     | Number 10: scsc
1011      | Number 11: scss
1100     | Number 12: sscc
1101      | Number 13: sscs
1110      | Number 14: sssc
1111       | Number 15: ssss
10000 | Number 16: scccc

Rules:
Take the binary result and replace every 0 with a c and replace every 1 with a s